headline: Sony’s Teenage Demon Hunter Beats Out Springsteen at Weekend Box Office
summary: An anime film about a teenage demon hunter and his dog beat out a Bruce Springsteen biopic and two other films to take the top slot at the domestic box office this weekend.  Sony’s   Chainsaw Man—The Movie: Reze Arc opened to $17.3 million in ticket sales domestically, according to Comscore, a month after its debut in Japan.  It beat out the second weekend for Universal’s Black Phone 2 and the debut for Paramount’s Regretting You, which came in second and third, respectively, with domestic sales of $13 million and $12.8 million for the weekend, Comscore said.
